      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Bypassing legal channels fundamentally erodes the social contract because it signals that laws are optional for some, thereby undermining the very foundation of a functioning, ordered society. When the rule of law is selectively applied, it invites chaos and weakens the authority of the state itself. Regarding security, unmonitored crossings create ungoverned spaces where criminal elements, including drug traffickers and terrorists, can operate with impunity, posing a direct and unacceptable threat to domestic public safety.",
      "source": "target",
